June 20 2003  03:33pm  Gary T. Thorne, This element was created for work associated with activity 6502.63., , This field contains the PROJECTS.LINE.ITEMS ID associated with a GL, number on a BPO. This information is necessary for the BPO.GL.HISTORY, file since a GL number may appear on multiple GL line items for a, BPO (if it is associated with different project information). When a, voucher is created for a BPO, BPO.GL.HISTORY records are created with, a BPOGL.TRAN.TYPE of 'O'riginal. These records do not have a reference, to the voucher from which they were created. However, if the voucher, amounts are maintained, S.POST.BPO uses these records to calculate, credit and debit amounts for an EP posting record to un-encumber or, relieve more encumbrances from the BPO. It uses the GL number as a, unique identifier for this. However, the GL number on a BPO is not, necessarily a unique identifier on BPO with project information. The, combination of GL number and project line item will become the unique, identifier for this logic.

Default Input Processing: IF LEN(EDITED.DATA) THEN,    * X.NEED.ID is used to determine whether we need to pass,    * the file ID and the user-assigned number through GLBU02,    * to compensate for the sequential keys to PO/BPO,    X.NEED.ID = '', $UC,    X.EDITED.DATA = TRIM(EDITED.DATA),    X.PREFIX = EDITED.DATA[1,1],    X.SUFFIX = EDITED.DATA[2,99],    * Recurring Voucher is stored as RV..., so we must also set,    *   variables to find this format,    X.RV.PREFIX = EDITED.DATA[1,2],    X.RV.SUFFIX = EDITED.DATA[3,99],    BEGIN CASE,  *,       CASE X.PREFIX = "E",     X.NEED.ID = '',     IF NUM(X.SUFFIX) THEN,   IF LEN(X.SUFFIX) LT 6 THEN,      X.SUFFIX = STR("0",6-LEN(X.SUFFIX)):X.SUFFIX,        END,     END,     IF LEN(X.SUFFIX) NE 6 THEN,        ERROR.OCCURRED = 1,   MSG = "Invalid Encumbrance Journal key format.",     END,     *,       CASE X.EE.SOURCE = "EN",     X.NEED.ID = '',     IF NOT(EDITED.DATA MATCHES "4N2A") THEN,   ERROR.OCCURRED = 1,        MSG = "Invalid payroll encumbrance reference number.",     END,     *,       CASE X.PREFIX = "P" OR X.PREFIX = "B",     BEGIN CASE,   CASE X.PREFIX = 'P',      X.NEED.ID = 'PO',   CASE X.PREFIX = 'B',      X.NEED.ID = 'BPO',     END CASE,     IF NUM(X.SUFFIX) THEN,   IF LEN(X.SUFFIX) LE 7 THEN,      X.SUFFIX = STR("0",7-LEN(X.SUFFIX)):X.SUFFIX,        END ELSE,      ERROR.OCCURRED = 1,      MSG = "Invalid Purchase Order key format.",   END,     END,     IF LEN(X.SUFFIX) GT 7 THEN,   ERROR.OCCURRED = 1,        MSG = "Invalid Purchase Order key format.",     END,     *,  CASE X.RV.PREFIX = "RV",     X.NEED.ID = '',     IF NUM(X.RV.SUFFIX) THEN,   IF LEN(X.RV.SUFFIX) LE 7 THEN, X.RV.SUFFIX = STR("0",7-LEN(X.RV.SUFFIX)):X.RV.SUFFIX,      * In order to set the proper key to EDITED.DATA below, must set,      * the ordinary prefix and suffix variables to the RV variables,      X.PREFIX = X.RV.PREFIX,      X.SUFFIX = X.RV.SUFFIX,        END ELSE,      ERROR.OCCURRED = 1,      MSG = "Invalid Recurring Voucher key format.",   END,     END ELSE,        ERROR.OCCURRED = 1,   MSG = "Invalid Recurring Voucher key format.",     END,     *,  CASE 1,     X.NEED.ID = '',     ERROR.OCCURRED = 1,     MSG = "Reference Number must be preceded by E, P, B or RV.",    END CASE,    IF NOT(ERROR.OCCURRED) THEN,       EDITED.DATA = X.PREFIX:X.SUFFIX,    END, END

This is a hold field to keep the date that the, INVT.REPORT.VALUE was set, which is when the, valuation report (INR019/INVR) is run.  The, valuation date is held in this report value date, field until INB014/INVU, which then writes it to, INVT.LAST.VALUE.DATE., , This is a work field for use by Colleague and not meant, to be modified by users.

This is a hold field to keep what's in INVT.VALUE at, the time the valuation report (INR019/INVR) is run., INVT.VALUE is calculated when inventory is received on, PORC, when inventory is issued on stock issues, and, when inventory adjustments are made, which means it, can change between INR019 and INB014 (INVU, the update, process).  So the valuation is held in this report, value field until INB014, which then writes it to, INVT.LAST.VALUE., , This is a work field for use by Colleague and not meant, to be modified by users.

Used by check print process.  This flag is set to N when, a voucher is flagged as not to be paid in Payment Flags, Maintenance (PYFM - APS004) and is null otherwise.  The, check print itself (APB022) has a list of vouchers with, the pay flag (VOU.PAY.FLAG) of N(o) and checks this, current pay flag to see if it is N.  If so, APB022 nulls, out the current pay flag and sets the pay flag to Y., This slightly convoluted method is used in response to, a user request that vouchers flagged as not to be paid, in APS004 get reset to be selected next time.  A way was, needed to not change vouchers that were already set to N, on entry to APS004 from being set back to Y.  So the, current run flag is used so only the vouchers that were, set from Y to N in APS004 get their flags set back to Y, in preparation for the next check print.

Toolcdd Lkup Pre Reso Hook: BEGIN CASE,    * Check for an "@" sign entry,    CASE EDITED.DATA EQ "@",       EDITED.DATA = CRNT.XEP.VENDORS.ID, ** NCCSO - Begin - LLEUNG SCR 201905, * If there is an alpha character followed by 9 digits, assume it's also an EP conglomerate vendor ID,    CASE EDITED.DATA MATCHES "1A9N",  NULL, * Check for ID records with wildcard '...' as part of ID entry,    CASE EDITED.DATA MATCHES "1A9N...",       NULL,    CASE EDITED.DATA MATCHES "...1A9N",  NULL,    CASE EDITED.DATA MATCHES "...9N",       NULL, ** NCCSO - End - LLEUNG SCR 201905,    * Assume an all numeric entry is an EP vendor ID,    CASE NUM(EDITED.DATA),  * Pad it to 9 digits,       IF LEN(EDITED.DATA) LT 9 THEN,     EDITED.DATA = STR("0",(9 - LEN(EDITED.DATA))):EDITED.DATA,  END,    * If there are 9 digits followed by an alpha character, assume it's,    * also an EP vendor ID,    CASE EDITED.DATA MATCHES "9N1A",       NULL,    * If the lookup data begins with a semicolon, take everything as-is,    CASE EDITED.DATA[1,1] EQ ";",       NULL,    * Anything else gets processed as a name lookup,    CASE 1,       X.NAME.LOOKUP = "",       CALL XS.GET.EP.NAME.LKUP.STRING(X.NAME.LOOKUP, EDITED.DATA),  EDITED.DATA = X.NAME.LOOKUP, END CASE
